At its best, cricket is a game of extreme tension. It is a game of immense skill, balance and concentration, with the victor usually the team who can best manage to cope with the pressure.

But I don’t want to talk about proper cricket. Like many other useless cricketers, I find it scary and alienating. We need something a bit less professional.
